               <p>LYDIA THOMPSON. My husband lives in <placeName id="t18200112-81-crimeloc459">Crescent-mews, Burton-crescent</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200112-81-crimeloc459" type="placeName" value="Crescent-mews, Burton-crescent"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200112-81-crimeloc459" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200112-81-off457 t18200112-81-crimeloc459"></join>. On the 3d of December a person hired a horse at our stable, I was in the stable - the prisoner is the man. I never saw him before. He said he was going to Barnet. I let him have a brown mare - he was to return it the same day. He never returned it.</p>
               <p>Q. When did you see the prisoner - A. At Marlborough-street, on the 7th of January. The man's hair was black. I never saw him with his hat off.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you hear the last trial - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. And yet you venture to swear he is the man - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200112-81-person822">
